Credit Ratings
HOUSTON INDUSTRIES Inc. (Houston) -- Moody's Investors
Service Inc. said it placed about $2.3 billion of debt and
securities issued by the Houston Lighting  Power Co. unit of
this utility concern under review for possible upgrade. The
debt under review include Houston Lighting's first mortgage
and collateralized bonds, secured pollution control issues
and secured medium-term notes -- all rated single-A-3.
Moody's is also reviewing Houston Lighting's preferred stock,
rated single-A-3. Moody's said it's assessing "the degree to
which the company's financial performance will be
strengthened by the more manageable construction program and
lower capital requirements anticipated over the next five
years."